  "texts": [
    "Note that the NL questions classification is anchored on the conceptual schema views.",
    "But, since these views map one-to-one to the tables of the relational schema, a classification anchored on the relational schema would remain the same.",
    "The classification is maintained for the other sets of views, even knowing that the definition of these other sets of views might simplify the translation of some NL questions (which was one of the reasons for considering these sets of views, in any case).",
    "Table 6.1 shows examples of NL questions and their ground truth SQL translations.",
    "Column \"ID\" indicates the question identifiers; column \"NL Question\" indicates the test NL questions suggested by experts; column \"Ground Truth SQL Query Table \" indicates the ground truth SQL query that represents the answer table for the NL question; and column \"Question Type\" represents the question type classification (as explained above)."
